Monuments.name: Santa Cruz
Monuments.description: The chapel of "Our Lady of Santa Cruz" is located at the top of the Djebel Murdjadjo, slightly below the former Spanish fort "Fort de Santa Cruz". The place is managed by the Diocese of Oran.

Monuments.name: La Cathédrale du Sacré Coeur
Monuments.description: The Cathedral of the Sacred Heart was built from 1904 to 1913 by the construction company of the Auguste brothers, it is the work of the architect Albert Ballu who was at the time the architect of the French government of Algeria

Monuments.name: 1st November Place
Monuments.description: The Place du 1er Novembre 1954 (ex-place d'Armes) is considered the historic heart of the city of Oran, it is at the crossroads of several roads that you came from the port, the waterfront and the city center.

Monuments.name: Pacha Mosque
Monuments.description: Located at the bottom of rue benamara Boutkhil, ex rue de Phillippe, the Pasha mosque that became a historical monument classified on 06/08/1952, captivates the curiosity of passers-by, its minaret dominates most houses and seduces the eye with the elegance of its proportions.

Monuments.name: The Great Synagogue of Oran
Monuments.description: The Great Synagogue of Oran (Arabic: معبد وهران العظيم), or locally the Great Synagogue, was built and dedicated in 1880 to the initiative of Simon Kanoui, but its inauguration took place only in 1918.

Monuments.name: Bey Palace
Monuments.description: The Bey Palace is a historic palace in Oran, Algeria, dating from the Ottoman era to the 18th century. The palace was classified as a national heritage in 2005.

Monuments.name: Arena of Oran
Monuments.description: The arenas of Oran is a circular building originally intended for the reception of bull races, located southwest of the city of Oran. These are the only arenas in Algeria and one of the few arenas on the African continent1. Built in 1890 of wood, following a fire it was rebuilt to its current state in 1908 and inaugurated in 1910.

Monuments.name: The Spanish Gate
Monuments.description: The Spanish Gate (originally called Ximénès Gate) is a monumental vaulted door located in the Sidi El Houari district (Dahli brothers street) and is currently one of the most important remains still preserved of Spanish architecture in Oran.
